  "text": "The liquid formulation of Sporanox achieves 30% higher blood concentrations. However, Sporanox solution is much more expensive than generic capsules. Also, the solution is often stopped because of poor palatability or toxicity. [CITATION_1] Gastrointestinal upset and fluid retention occur more commonly with the solution than the capsules. Itraconazole solution should be given on an empty stomach to achieve the highest serum concentration.",
  "correct_citation": {
